<HEADLINE>
<P>
GAIN STUDENTS, STAFF REPLY TO ARTICLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Your article was appalling. I found it to be inaccurate and misleading. You 
based your information on facts from one class and only a few others spoken to. 
</P>
<P>
First, not everyone who attends GAIN falls under the categories written about. 
I volunteered to participate in this program. I am neither illiterate nor 
uneducated to the point of not knowing how to add or subtract. 
</P>
<P>
I do not use drugs. I have not been to jail or have any type of record or 
history of violence or an attitude problem. 
</P>
<P>
Our school is not a school of last resort. It is a second chance for us to 
better ourselves and our life situations. I sincerely suggest you recheck your 
facts and stop prejudging others. This prejudging causes prejudice, which can 
hurt this valuable program. 
</P>
<P>
TINA HAWN 
</P>
<P>
Oxnard 
</P>
</TEXT>
