<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRESIDENTIAL RACE HIGHLIGHTS SOCCER MEETING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE CART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A presidential election -- expected to generate a hotly contested three-way 
race -- will be the highlight of the U.S. Soccer Federation's annual general 
meeting, beginning today in Orlando, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
The four-day meeting will end Sunday with the election of officers. The 
presidential election is especially significant, since whoever is elected will 
preside over the 1994 World Cup, to be held in the United States. 
</P>
<P>
There are three announced candidates for president: current USSF President 
Werner Fricker, USSF Treasurer Paul Stiehl, and former Clipper president Alan 
Rothenberg. 
</P>
<P>
The elections are expected to set the agenda for soccer in this country for the 
next four years. JULIE CART 
</P>
</TEXT>
