<P>
Oklahoma running back Mike Gaddis has not recovered from a knee injury that cut 
his season in half last year and will miss the entire 1990 football season, 
Coach Gary Gibbs said. 
</P>
<P>
"Based on my observation and some conversation with the doctor and Mike, I 
don't feel he will be ready to participate at all this coming season," Gibbs 
said. "He's not nearly where he needs to be. He has a long way to go." 
</P>
<P>
Gaddis, a junior from Midwest City, will have one year of college eligibility 
remaining because he used 1987 as a redshirt year. 
</P>
<P>
Gaddis was the nation's second-leading rusher last season through six games 
with 829 yards when he injured his knee against Texas. 
