<P>
Two Ex-Hughes Employees Indicted: The Justice Department and the Arizona 
Attorney General's Office said two former employees of Hughes Aircraft were 
charged with conspiring to defraud the Environmental Protection Agency by 
concealing information about hazardous waste accidents. The two, Robert E. 
Morrison of Longmont, Colo., and Jay L. Barnett of Tucson, worked at a Hughes 
Aircraft Missile Systems Group factory in Tucson. Hazardous waste was released 
into the environment from treatment units that the two men allegedly were 
supervising, the indictment said. 
