<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: LEGAL FILE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
'Rockford' Legal Files: The creator of the 1970s "Rockford Files" TV series has 
sued Universal Studios, claiming he is owed $5 million in profits. 
</P>
<P>
The Los Angeles Superior Court suit claims Roy Huggins originated the series 
concept, and was promised 25% of net profits from the detective show. Huggins 
claims the show, which ran from 1974 to 1980, grossed more than $120 million. A 
Universal attorney refused to comment. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
