<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: LEGAL FILE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
'Aliens' Fight in Court: Sigourney Weaver, along with the director and 
producers of "Aliens," have sued 20th Century Fox Film Corp. claiming the 
studio withheld their shares of the movie's net profits. 
</P>
<P>
The Los Angeles Superior Court lawsuit claims the film company has breached 
contracts with Weaver, writer-director James Cameron, producer Gale Anne Hurd 
and executive producer Gordon Carroll. Weaver claims she was entitled to 10% of 
the film's net profits. Cameron was entitled to 10.5% and Hurd to 5 %, 
according to the suit. Studio officials could not be reached for comment. GREG 
BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
