<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Baby Boss: Evan James Springsteen. That's the name of the baby born to Bruce 
Springsteen and Patti Scialfa. 
</P>
<P>
The birth was announced last week, but the name and other details weren't 
available until Wednesday. A spokeswoman for the singers said the baby had 
brown hair and blue eyes and was born at 5:03 a.m., July 25 in a Los Angeles 
hospital. Both Springsteen and Scialfa have albums due in the coming months. No 
word on how the baby's birth will affect the completion of the albums or tour 
plans. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA080290-0097 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 255871 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
August 2, 1990, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
