<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE NEIGHBORHOOD EATERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KENT ZELAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
King Neptune's Seafood Restaurant and Nautical Museum, 17115 Pacific Coast 
Highway, Sunset Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Open daily 11 a.m. to 2 a.m. Dinners are served after 5. (213) 592-4878. 
Started as a place for the ex-Marine owner to display his huge collection of 
nautical/military artifacts, this bar-restaurant-museum is one of the least 
pretentious, and most bizarre, places in Orange County or maybe anywhere. Basic 
seafood, like the ambience, comes in generous portions. KENT ZELAS 
</P>
</TEXT>
