<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRANSIENT HELD IN PHOTO SHOP THEFTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COSTA MESA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man suspected of robbing photo-development shops in four cities was arrested 
Wednesday afternoon, police reported. 
</P>
<P>
The suspect, Patrick Nicholas, 28, a transient, was caught about half an hour 
after a Photo Stop store at 201 E. 17th St. was robbed about 5 p.m., said Sgt. 
Tim Holbrook. 
</P>
<P>
Holbrook said that after a police broadcast of the description of the suspect 
and his getaway car, an officer spotted Nicholas at a nearby shopping center 
and arrested him without incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
ROBBERIES -- ORANGE COUNTY; HOMELESS -- ORANGE COUNTY 
