<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIP LEFEBVRE TO COACH AT SANTA MARGARITA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tip Lefebvre has been hired as the baseball coach at Santa Margarita High 
School, Athletic Director Rich Schaaf said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Lefebvre, brother of Seattle Mariner Manager Jim Lefebvre, has been an 
assistant coach at UCLA the past three years. He replaces Ray Huntington, who 
resigned at the end of last season. A former catcher in the Dodger 
organization, Tip Lefebvre was the pitching coach for the Phoenix Giants in 
1984-86. He also was the head coach at Pius X High from 1969-72. 
</P>
<P>
The Eagles were 8-15 overall and 6-8 in the Olympic League last season, their 
first on the varsity level. Santa Margarita, which opened in 1987, will have 
its first senior class this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
