<HEADLINE>
<P>
BIKE WHIZ-IN TO OFFER SOME OLDER WHEELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Vintage and antique bicycles will be shown at the 13th annual Whiz-In at the 
Elks Lodge in Fountain Valley on Saturday and Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The event will feature a ride of vintage motorbikes Saturday and a show and 
swap meet Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The show will include antique and nostalgic bicycles and all types of motorized 
bikes. Whizzers are a motorized version of Schwinn bicycles made in 1939-52, 
according to event organizer Sterling Pope. An engine kit or Whizzer could be 
bolted on to any bike of that era. 
</P>
<P>
Last year, the event attracted 65 vendors of vintage bicycles and parts. 
Admission is $2. 
</P>
<P>
The event will be held from 7 a.m. to 3 p.m. Saturday and Sunday at the Elks 
Lodge, 10480 Talbert Ave., at the San Diego Freeway in Fountain Valley. For 
details, call Pope at (714) 642-0783. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, This kerosene lamp is clamped onto the front fork of a 1898 Gormully 
&amp; Jeffery "Rambler" bicycle. MARK BOSTER / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
