<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: LA VERNE; 
</P>
<P>
HOUSING SUIT PUT ON HOLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A legal dispute between Lewis Homes of California and the city will be on hold 
until Jan. 8, 1991, under a formal settlement agreement adopted Monday night by 
the City Council. 
</P>
<P>
The agreement gives the city time to review a modified housing development plan 
Lewis has submitted for a tract in the foothills west of Esperanza Drive and 
north of Base Line Road. 
</P>
<P>
The company sued after the city failed to approve an earlier development plan. 
</P>
<P>
Among other changes, Lewis' new plan proposes 186 hillside houses instead of 
230, a development area of 61.9 acres instead of 75.4 and 151 acres retained as 
open area instead of 137. The plan must still go through Planning Commission 
review Wednesday, and a City Council public hearing Nov. 5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
