<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
TEMPORARY JURIST TO REPLACE AILING JUDGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Glendale Municipal Court officials have been authorized to appoint a temporary 
jurist to replace an ill judge who has been unable to work. 
</P>
<P>
A temporary court commissioner is expected to be named by Aug. 20 to replace 
Judge Cheryl Krott, who has been off the bench since June 22. 
</P>
<P>
The court's presiding judge, Charles E. Horan, declined to describe the 
illness. 
</P>
<P>
Krott has had two surgeries since last August, Horan said. It is uncertain 
whether or how soon she will return to the courtroom. Retired Judge Samuel 
Laidig has substituted for Krott but will leave the position Aug. 17, Horan 
said. The Los Angeles County Board of Supervisors voted July 24 to authorize a 
temporary jurist. 
</P>
<P>
Krott joined the bench in 1983 as a commissioner and was made a judge in 1986, 
court officials said. 
</P>
