<P>
SANTA MONICA OKS KRISHNA FESTIVAL PARADE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Santa Monica City Council Tuesday night authorized a parade to be held 
Sunday at 11 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
The council approved a request from the International Society for Krishna 
Consciousness to run the parade for its Festival of the Chariots. The parade 
will begin at the beach parking lot at the western terminus of Bay Street and 
proceed south along the bike path onto the Venice boardwalk. 
</P>
<P>
The 14th-annual parade will end at Venice Pavilion Park, where there will be 
entertainment, elephant rides and exhibits on topics including vegetarianism, 
reincarnation and animal protection. 
</P>
