<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA080290-0169 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 256051 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
August 2, 1990, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Southeast; Part J; Page 8; Column 3 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
110 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
FHP FOUNDATION GIVES $265,000 IN AID 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONG BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The FHP Foundation awarded more than $265,000 in grants at its quarterly board 
of directors meeting. 
</P>
<P>
California Pools for the Handicapped, operating in Long Beach, received $25,000 
in support of warm-water hydrotherapy programs for senior citizens. 
</P>
<P>
Other local recipients included Young Horizons of Lakewood and the Los Angeles 
Poison Control Center. The Los Angeles Free Clinic accepted $15,000 for its 
medication information service, a caller-directed program that answers consumer 
questions about drug interactions and side effects. 
</P>
<P>
The FHP Foundation supports education, research and development of community 
activities related to health care. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
