<HEADLINE>
<P>
GETTING ON LINE WITH USERS GROUPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Linda Murphy 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Don't know a computer chip from a chocolate chip? Having trouble finding 
software for your brontosaurus of a machine that is nearly extinct? Want to 
find out how to turn your personal computer into a home music studio? Eager to 
sharpen your programming skills? 
</P>
<P>
If so, chances are there is a computer users group or special interest group 
(SIG) in the area to meet your needs. 
</P>
<P>
Listed are several users groups that meet in the North County. If you don't see 
one that suits you, contact the San Diego Computer Society (549-3787) or the 
San Diego Macintosh User Group (287-4626) for help, or attend one of their 
meetings. 
</P>
<P>
Commodore 64 Seniors -- For seniors who use the Commodore 64 computer. Meetings 
are held the second and fourth Thursdays of each month at 2 p.m. in Escondido. 
Contact Kae Allred at 480-6368 for meeting place. 
</P>
<P>
Disabled Interest Group -- Contact Pat Mathias at 743-3217 for information on 
the San Diego Disabled Interest Group (DIG-SIG), which meets the first 
Wednesday of each month at 7 p.m. at the Senior Center of the North Park 
Recreation Center, 2719 Howard Ave., San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
ERACE (Electronic Resources Atari Computer Enthusiasts) -- For all Atari 
computer users. Meetings are held the second Thursday of each month at 6 p.m. 
at the NCC computer store, 1830 Hacienda Drive, Vista. Contact Gary Martin at 
489-9872 after 6 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
K-North -- For users of Kaypro and other MS-DOS computers. Meetings are held 
the fourth Tuesday of each month at 7 p.m. at 531 Vista Bella, Oceanside. 
Contact Bob Boomer at 941-6161. 
</P>
<P>
MUSIC (MIDI Users Special Interest Consortium) -- For those interested in 
forming a MIDI (Musical Instrument Digital Interface) group in the North 
County, call Scott Garside at 673-8275. 
</P>
<P>
North Coast Kaypro Users Group -- For those interested in Kaypro CP/M 
computers. Contact George Guy at 755-4911 for information. 
</P>
<P>
North County Appleholics -- For Apple computer users. Meetings are held the 
first Thursday of each month at 7 p.m. Contact Tony Diaz at 439-0304 for 
meeting place. 
</P>
<P>
North County Commodore 64 SIG -- For Commodore 64 and 128 users. Meetings are 
held the third Monday of each month at 7 p.m. at 3340 Jasmine Place, Escondido. 
Contact Ron Silva at 747-2094. 
</P>
<P>
North County IBM PC SIG -- For all IBM and compatible computer users. Meetings 
are held the second Friday of each month at 6:30 p.m. at MiraCosta College, 
Room E-9, One Barnard Drive, Oceanside. Contact George King at 931-1000. 
</P>
<P>
North County TI-99ers -- For users of Texas Instruments 99 computers. Meetings 
are held the first and third Wednesday of each month at 7 p.m. at Coco's Family 
Restaurant, 1340 E. Valley Parkway Escondido. Contact Charley Summerhill at 
745-6654 or Richard Hay at 487-6058. 
</P>
<P>
North San Diego Apple Club -- For Apple II computer users. Meetings are held 
the first Thursday of each month at 6:30 p.m. at Ericson Elementary School, 
11174 Westonhill Drive, Mira Mesa. Contact Bill Walker at 579-9649 or Lee 
Dronick at 695-1485. 
</P>
<P>
Personal Ancestral File Genealogy Group -- For users of the Personal Ancestral 
File software program, and others interested in using computers to study their 
family history. Meetings are held the fourth Tuesday of each month at 7 p.m. at 
the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints, 1917 E. Washington Ave., 
Escondido. Contact Berta Lee MacDonald at 746-4317. 
</P>
<P>
Ramona Amiga Users Group -- For all Amiga computer users. Meetings are held the 
second Wednesday of each month at 7 p.m. at the SIGH Amiga store, 677-B Main 
St., Ramona. Contact Nick Jensen at 788-0447. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego Macintosh Users Group North County SIG -- For Macintosh computer 
users. Meetings are held the first Monday of each month at 7 p.m. at 802 E. 
Grand Ave., Escondido. Contact Leo Lamboy at 743-5557. 
</P>
<P>
Tandy Users Group -- For all Tandy computer users. Meetings are held the second 
Saturday of each month at 9 a.m. at the Great American Bank, 2751 Via De La 
Valle, Del Mar. Contact Nick Sacorafas at 942-5798 after 7 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The San Diego Computer Society, through which many of the above groups are 
affiliated, meets on the third Saturday of each month at 11:30 a.m. at Sea 
World's A Place to Meet. The San Diego Macintosh User Group, parent 
organization for San Diego County's Macintosh SIGs, holds its meetings the 
first Wednesday of each month at 7 p.m. at the UCSD Price Center Theater. Linda 
Murphy 
</P>
</TEXT>
