<HEADLINE>
<P>
30 FEARED DEAD IN SOVIET PLANE CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MOSCOW 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Soviet passenger plane carrying 30 people from Armenia to the disputed 
territory of Nagorno-Karabakh crashed into a mountain Wednesday, killing 
everyone aboard, a member of the Armenian Parliament said. 
</P>
<P>
Karen Simonyan said that wreckage from the aircraft, a Yak-40, and several 
bodies were found in rugged territory near Agdam, a town just outside 
Nagorno-Karabakh in the republic of Azerbaijan. 
</P>
<P>
The Armenian government and Soviet aviation officials declined to confirm that 
the aircraft had crashed, saying only that the plane was missing and that a 
search was continuing. 
</P>
