3 OFFICERS SLAIN IN AMBUSH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GUATEMALA CITY 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The police chief in the Caribbean coastal town of Puerto Barrios and two 
officers were ambushed and killed by a group of heavily armed men while 
patrolling an area considered a route for contraband and narcotics, a police 
spokesman said Wednesday. 
</P>
