<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: PIT BULL KILLED AFTER BITING OFFICER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A pit bull terrier -- allegedly urged on by its owner -- bit an Inglewood 
police officer Sunday night before officers shot and killed the dog, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Alex Olemedo Lorenzo, 29, of Inglewood was charged with assault with a deadly 
weapon for allegedly ordering the dog to attack Officer Jacqueline Layne, 22. 
She suffered puncture wounds in both arms. 
</P>
<P>
Police said Layne and her partner were flagged down by a man in the 3900 block 
of West Century Boulevard who complained that the suspect was harassing people 
with an unleashed pit bull. Lorenzo allegedly threatened the officers with the 
dog as they approached and told the dog to charge them, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
