<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE IN THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Items for People in the News should be mailed to the Los Angeles Times, South 
Bay office, 23133 Hawthorne Blvd., Torrance, 90505. 
</P>
<P>
Pat Chandler has been named director of educational services for the South Bay 
Union High School District. 
</P>
<P>
She will fill the position created by the Aug. 30 retirement of L'Cena Rice. 
Chandler has been with the district four years, as assistant principal at 
Redondo Beach High School, principal of Pacific Shores High School/ director of 
alternative education, and last year as director of curriculum and instruction 
at the district. Other new assignments include: Jerry Goddard, to replace 
Sharon Dezutti as director of personnel; assignment of Dezutti as associate 
superintendent for personnel, and LeGayle Black, who will become director of 
fiscal and administrative services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
