<HEADLINE>
<P>
COOK IT LIGHT: DO-AHEAD POTATO DISH IS NO-FUSS CHOICE FOR PARTIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNE JONES, Jones is a food consultant and a cookbook author. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
When you want to get everything ready ahead of time, such as before a weekend 
party, my potato recipe is the perfect choice. These Make-Ahead Potatoes are 
first baked, then scooped out of their shells and seasoned, stuffed back in, 
wrapped and refrigerated until just before you need them. Simply allow them to 
return to room temperature, unwrap and place under the broiler for a few 
minutes, until they are hot and ready to serve. 
</P>
<P>
MAKE-AHEAD POTATOES 
</P>
<P>
3 large baking potatoes 
</P>
<P>
Canola oil 
</P>
<P>
1 medium onion, thinly sliced 
</P>
<P>
2 tablespoons corn-oil margarine 
</P>
<P>
1/3 cup non-fat milk 
</P>
<P>
3/4 teaspoon salt 
</P>
<P>
1/4 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper 
</P>
<P>
1/2 teaspoon liquid smoke 
</P>
<P>
6 tablespoons freshly grated Parmesan cheese 
</P>
<P>
Paprika, optional 
</P>
<P>
Thoroughly scrub potatoes. Dry with paper towels. Rub skin of each potato with 
canola oil. 
</P>
<P>
Cut each potato in half lengthwise and evenly divide onion slices between 6 
potato halves. Put each potato back together, enclosing onion slices between 
halves and wrap tightly with aluminum foil. Place potatoes in baking dish or on 
baking sheet, place in center of oven and bake at 400 degrees 1 hour. 
</P>
<P>
Remove potatoes from oven and unwrap. Remove onions and place in large mixing 
bowl. Scoop out cooked pulp from each potato half, being careful not to tear 
skins, then add pulp to onion. Reserve 6 potato skins. 
</P>
<P>
Add margarine to potatoes and onions. Combine milk with salt, pepper and liquid 
smoke. Mix well and add to potato mixture. 
</P>
<P>
Using electric mixer or potato masher, whip potato mixture until thoroughly 
mixed and smooth in texture. Divide potato mixture evenly between 6 reserved 
skins and, if making ahead, re-wrap in foil and refrigerate until 1 hour prior 
to serving. 
</P>
<P>
To serve, unwrap potatoes and sprinkle 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese on top of 
each potato half. Sprinkle with paprika. Place potato halves under broiler 
until warm and lightly browned.Makes 6 servings. 
</P>
<P>
 Each serving contains approximately 244 calories; 4 mg cholesterol; 6 gm fat; 
454 mg sodium. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Recipe 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA080290-0230 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 256202 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
August 2, 1990, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
