<P>
POLICE READY; ZODIAC KILLER ISN'T 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Scores of detectives and hundreds of police officers spread out across the city 
in anticipation of a fifth attack by the Zodiac killer this morning, but the 
astrology-obsessed gunman did not strike. 
</P>
<P>
The pre-dawn hours of today were considered a target night for the gunman, 
based on his pattern of striking on early Thursdays at 21-day intervals or 
multiples thereof. 
</P>
<P>
Today marked 42 days since the gunman's attack on a homeless man sleeping on a 
Central Park bench. It is also in the sign of Leo, believed to be the 
astrological sign of the gunman's next victim. 
</P>
<P>
The gunman has sent six letters to police and the media, threatening to kill 12 
people, one for each astrological sign. 
</P>
</TEXT>
