CARSON GOES APE TO AID CHIMP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ROYAL, Neb. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Johnny Carson didn't monkey around when a zoo in his native Nebraska needed 
help. 
</P>
<P>
He donated $55,000 to give Reuben the chimp new digs. 
</P>
<P>
Northeast Nebraska Zoo has only one chimpanzee, but the donation from "The 
Tonight Show" host may be enough to acquire a female companion for Reuben as 
well as build a permanent primate exhibit, zoo officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The 7-year-old chimp is housed in a fortified mobile home at the zoo in rural 
Royal, near Carson's hometown of Norfolk, but the monkey has grown too strong 
for his quarters. 
</P>
<P>
Construction should begin next week on a new enclosure. 
</P>
