OPRAH GIFT AIDS BATTERED WOMEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
INVER GROVE HEIGHTS, Minn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A $20,000 donation from talk show host Oprah Winfrey will help open a new 
shelter for battered women. 
</P>
<P>
The B. Robert Lewis House, a private agency headquartered in Eagan, will open 
its second shelter in an abandoned convent, director Mary Ajax said. The 
convent is being leased for 20 cents a year from church officials who wished to 
remain anonymous, she said. 
</P>
<P>
The windfall came last November when Winfrey held a benefit performance in 
Minneapolis and offered to give half of the proceeds to the shelter. 
</P>
<P>
Ajax said the donation was so large that it took several months for the shelter 
to find other sources to match it. 
</P>
