<TEXT>
<P>
Darryl Strawberry broke out of a slump with a two-run homer and an RBI single 
and Frank Viola became the first National League pitcher to win 15 games as the 
New York Mets beat the Montreal Expos 5-1 today. 
</P>
<P>
Strawberry, who was 0-for-18, snapped a 1-1 tie with a run-scoring single off 
Dennis Martinez (7-8) during a two-run sixth inning, then slammed his 26th 
homer in a three-run eighth. 
</P>
<P>
Viola (15-5) allowed six hits, struck out seven and walked one in pitching his 
sixth complete game for the East Division-leading Mets. 
</P>
<P>
Howard Johnson began New York's rally in the sixth with a one-out single 
against Martinez, who had blanked the Mets on three hits over the first five 
innings. Johnson stole second as Dave Magadan struck out. 
</P>
<P>
Gregg Jefferies then drove in Johnson with a triple before Strawberry singled, 
making it 2-1. 
</P>
<P>
Kevin McReynolds also homered for the Mets in the eighth. 
</P>
